&thorn;at ilke houre &thorn;ou sa&llbar; thynke of &thorn;e
witsonnday, how &thorn;e ty&mtail; of &thorn;e day oure Lorde Ihesu
Criste sente &thorn;e Haly Gaste ti&llbar; His disciples, in liknes of
fyre, and of tunnges, in takynnynge &thorn;at &thorn;ay sulde hafe
abowndance in worde and brynnynge in lufe, and &thorn;at ryghte es
&thorn;e purueance of oure Lorde puruayde; For in twa maners &thorn;e
wykked gaste begylede ma&ntail; in paradyse, &thorn;at es to saye,
with wykke&dtail; entycement of his tunge, and with &thorn;e caldnes
of his veny&mtail;.  And for-&thorn;i come &thorn;e Haly Gaste in
lyknes of tung, agayne &thorn;e Entycement of &thorn;e deuelle, and in
fyre for to distruye &thorn;e caldnes of his veny&mtail;.  &para;
Be-fore myddaye sa&llbar; &thorn;ou thynke of &thorn;e
Anunciacyo&ntail;, and of Ihesu passio&ntail;.  And of &thorn;e
Anunciacio&ntail; sa&llbar; &thorn;ou thynke of &thorn;e grete mercy
of oure Lorde Ihesu Criste, whi &thorn;at He walde be-comme ma&ntail;,
and For vs suffire &thorn;e dede in &thorn;at swete manhe&dtail;
Se&ntail; He moghte hafe boghte vs agayne on o&thorn;er manere.  And
&thorn;at dyde He for ti&llbar; drawe ti&llbar; Hy&mtail; &thorn;i
luffe.  For if ane hade bene &thorn;i maker, and ano&thorn;er thi
byere, and hade sufferde in thaire bodyes a&llbar; oure sorowe for to
by a&llbar; oure lufe, Than hade noghte oure trouthe bene anely in
ane.  Off &thorn;e passio&ntail; sa&llbar; &thorn;ou thynke at
&thorn;at houre how oure Lorde Ihesu was done one &thorn;e Crosse
be-twyx twa thefes, ane one His ryghte syde, and ano&thorn;er one His
lefte syde, and Hym-selfe &thorn;ay hangede be-twix &thorn;a&mtail;
twa, alls mayster of thefes.  For if all &thorn;e sekenes of &thorn;is
werlde and a&llbar; &thorn;e sorowe ware in &thorn;e body of a
ma&ntail; anely, and &thorn;at man myghte consayfe


 
<!-- 0023.p44-45.txt -->
<PB N="44">


alls meki&llbar; noye and Angwysce and Sorowe in his body als a&llbar;
&thorn;e me&ntail; of &thorn;is werlde moghte thynke, &yogh;itt it
ware fu&llbar; litti&llbar; or e&llbar;s noghte to regarde of &thorn;e
sorowe &thorn;at He sufferde for vs ane houre of &thorn;e daye.
&para; Before nonne sa&llbar; &thorn;ou thynke of &thorn;e
passio&ntail; and of &thorn;e gloriouse Ascencio&ntail;.  Of &thorn;e
passione sa&llbar; &thorn;ou thynke, &thorn;at at swylke a ty&mtail;
of &thorn;e daye dyede &thorn;e makere of lyfe, for &thorn;i lufe.
And here sa&llbar; &thorn;ou thynke of &thorn;e wordes &thorn;at Ihesu
spake o&ntail; &thorn;e crose, and of &thorn;e foure takynes &thorn;at
be-fe&llbar;e in His dede.  The fyrste worde was &thorn;is &thorn;at
He spake, `Fadire, for-gyffe &thorn;a&mtail; &thorn;is sy&ntail;, for
&thorn;ay wate noghte whate &thorn;ay doo.'  The to&thorn;er worde was
&thorn;is, &thorn;at He said to &thorn;e thefe, `For sothe I say the,
&thorn;is day sa&llbar; &thorn;ou be with me in paradyse.'  The thirde
