dou&ntail;, &thorn;e stanes raue in soundire, &thorn;e graues opyned
and &thorn;e dede men rase, and &thorn;e sonne with-drewe his lyghte
fra &thorn;e werlde fra myddaye to noune.  Of &thorn;e Ascencione
sa&llbar; &thorn;ou thynke that swylke a ty&mtail; of &thorn;e daye
wente vpe oure Lorde Ihesu Criste in-ti&llbar; &thorn;e mounte of
Olyuete, Seande His discyples and His swete modire Marie, how He
steig&hbar;e in-ti&llbar; heue&ntail;, and sett Hym one Fadir righte
hande; and how His dysciples turnede agayne into &thorn;e Cete, and
ware in fastynge and in prayere vnti&llbar; &thorn;e commynge of
&thorn;e Haly Gaste; and &thorn;are ware togedire a hundret&hbar; and
twentty in a house for to abyde &thorn;e commynge of &thorn;e Haly
Gaste, als oure Lorde commande &thorn;a&mtail; before.  &para; Before
euensnage sa&llbar; &thorn;ou thynke of Ihesu passio&ntail; and of His
supere.  Of &thorn;e passio&ntail; sa&llbar; &thorn;ou thynke how
Iosep&hbar;
<PB N="45">



of Aramathy purchaste Ihesu body of Pilate, and how &thorn;ey come to
&thorn;e crosse &thorn;are He hange, and &thorn;ay brakke &thorn;e twa
thee-banes of &thorn;e twa thefes.  And &thorn;are was a knyghte redye
